## ðŸ›  Steps Taken (task 4)
1.Created a resource group.
.Resource Group Name - AZ500Lab01. Location - East US
2. Assigned the Service Desk Virtual Machine Contributor permissions.
.On the Resource groups, selected the AZ500LAB01 resource group entry.
.On the AZ500Lab01 blade, selected Access control (IAM) in the middle pane.
.On the AZ500Lab01 | Access control (IAM) blade, clicked + Add and then, in the drop-down menu, clicked Add role assignment.
.Role - Virtual Machine Contributor. Assigned Access to Service Desk
.Viewed the check access tab on the AZ500Lab01 Access Control and searched for Dylan Williams, to confirm the assignment.

## ðŸ›  Steps Taken (task 5)
1. Deleted the resource group created in the lab
. Opened Powershell
.Remove-AZResourceGroup -Name "AZ500LAB01" -Force -AsJob

## ðŸ“š Key Learnings
- How RBAC enforces least privilege in Azure.
- Difference between built-in and custom roles.

